@NODE reading "RECOMMENDED READING"

    RIPSCRIP 1.54 specifications text file. Available on my bbs (and
others) for downloading as RIPSC154.LHA. It covers much of the protocol
which I may have assumed you understood in this document.

    See @{" PROGRAM SUPPORT " link support} for BBS phone numbers.

@ENDNODE

@NODE feedback "FEEDBACK"

    RIPGRAF is very much a work in progress (as you can see). The
operation of the program was based entirely on how *I* thought the program
should work, this was not on purpose it was because I was not getting on
feedback (people offered to be beta testers but only for the purposes of
getting the most recent versions and not to help with the development! :-P)

    You, as a RIPGRAF user, stand a much better chance of having the
operation of the program changed now rather than when I release version
1.0. So tell me what you want and you may just see included in a future
version (not necessarily the NEXT release).

@ENDNODE

@NODE registering "REGISTRATION"

